Reply to, archive, and restore questions in Slido
As a Webex Meetings or Webex Webinars host, you can reply to any question your participants submit in Slido. After you've replied to the question, mark it as answered to make room for the next question.
Slido is available in Webex Meetings. You can use Slido in plans for up to 10,000 users in Webex Webinars on version 41.9 and later sites. Slido polls are available for up to 10,000 attendees, while quizzes are available for up to 5,000 users.
Before you begin
Make sure you've turned on the Q&A feature in Slido.
1
During a meeting or webinar, go to the Q&A tab in Slido, select the Live question, and then click Reply .

  If you don't want to reply to a question right now but you want to save it for later, click Archive .
2
Type your reply, choose whether to send your reply from the Moderator or use your name, and then click Send .

  You can change Moderator to another alias. Click next to Moderator to change it.
3
Click Mark as answered to move the question to the Archive tab.
4
Restore a question by going to the Archive tab and clicking Restore .
Questions that were live reappear in the Live tab. Questions under review reappear in the Review tab.